<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-31-0142 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Biology and Medicine Division continues to make important contributionsin scientific areas in which it has a long-established leadership role.For 50 years the Division has pioneered in the application of radioisotopesand charged particles to biology and medicine. There is a growing emphasison cellular and molecular applications in the work of all the Division'sresearch groups. The powerful tools of genetic engineering, the use ofrecombinant products, the analytical application of DNA probes, and theuse of restriction fragment length polymorphic DNA are described andproposed for increasing use in the future.</TEXT></DOC>